    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#Expression>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"The intellectual realisation of a Work in the form of identifiable immaterial objects, such as, but not limited to, text.\n\nThe substance of Expression is signs.\n\nAn Expression cannot exist without a physical carrier but do not depend on a specific physical carrier and can exist on one or more carriers simultaneously."@en .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10250>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first>	<http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10249> .
