    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#refers_to>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Any entity that this work or expression refers to ; typically references are made to other Works, but it can be also to legislative processes, persons, etc.\n\nNote that specific subproperties exist in ELI-DL to describe future legal impacts (\\\"foresees_xxxx\\\" links) and links between amendments and draft legislation.\n\nExample : an opinion refers to the specific version of the draft legislation on which it is based."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#jurisdiction>	<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#historyNote>	"v1.3 : Updated link to EU vocabularies website in the definition."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#latest_activity>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates the latest activity that took place within a process. This is used to indicate to a reader the latest stage of a process.\nDepending on the point of view, this can be used to point to the ongoing activity (not finished yet), or to the latest activity that actually completed."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#process_title>	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/identifier>	"process_title" .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#countersigned_by>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalResource> .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10201>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#date_applicability>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"The date at which the legislation becomes applicable. This is distinct from the date of entry into force : a text may come in force today, and state it will become applicable in 3 months.\n\nThe group notes that applicability dates can lead to complex situations, e.g. a text with different applicability dates for different jurisdictions; specific extensions to the model should be used for such situations."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalValue-authoritative>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"created in v1.0"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#format>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"created in v1.0" .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#implemented_by>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"modified in v1.1"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#Work>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"created in v1.3" .
