    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#legal_value>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"The legal value associated with a specific format of a resource. A set of values is defined by ELI in the corresponding concept scheme. These values are :\n  - unofficial : no particular or special standing;\n  - official : published by an organisation with the public task of making the information available (e.g. a consolidated version of a EU directive) ;\n  - authoritative : the publisher gives some special status to the publication (e.g. \"the Queens Printer\" version of an Act of Parliament, or the OJ version of a EU Directive);\n  - definitive : the text is conclusively what the law says, (e.g. the digitally signed version of an OJ)."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#DecisionMethod>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"A method to carry out a decision; the way a decision was made."@en .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10274>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxCardinality>	"1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer> .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10091>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#rest>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#date_publication>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"modified in v1.1"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_voter_favor>	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/identifier>	"had_voter_favor" .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#forms_part_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates another larger activity that encompasses this one. \n\nExample : the activity \\\"Readng in commission of legislative process 384\\\" forms part of \\\"First lecture in assembl\u00E9e nationale of legislative process 384\\\", which itself forms part \\\"Legislative process number 384\\\"."@en .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10103>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalResource> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_participation>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"The participation of an Agent in an activity"@en .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10268>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxCardinality>	"1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer> .
