    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#changes>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates that this work or expression legally changes another. This encompasses the notions of amendment, replacement, repeal, or other types of change. This may be a direct change (textual or non-textual amendment) or a consequential or indirect change. Note, the property is to be used to express the existence of a change relationship between two acts rather than the existence of a consolidated version of the text that shows the result of the change. For consolidation relationships, use the \"consolidates\" and \"consolidated_by\" properties."@en .
