    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#format>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"The format of the manifestation, expressed as a custom URI.\nThis field is intended to capture the format of the resource from an application or user perspective, as opposed to the \"media_type\" property that expresses its format from a technical point of view. This property allows to describe different XML schemas (Akoma N'toso vs. proprietary), describe different types of PDFs (scanned PDF, generated-on-the-fly PDF, signed PDF, archival PDF) or describe the paper (printed) version of the legislation.\nELI includes a set of possible values for the most common use-cases and possible URIs values CAN also be taken from http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types , or can de defined by the Member States."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#documented_by_a_realization_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf>	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P33_used_specific_technique> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_responsible_person>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#Person> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#Vote>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>	"Vote"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_participation>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#Activity> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#number_of_votes_against>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"The total number of votes against"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#draft_amended_by>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#AmendmentToDraftLegislationWork> .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10193>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalResource> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#licence>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>	"licence"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_responsible_organization>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#Organization> .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10140>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#unionOf>	<http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10142> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_legal_basis>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates an act that specified the legislative workflow in which this activity takes place.\n\nExample : \\\"The Signature by the President of the European Parliament and the President of the Council of Procedure 2016/0382/COD had the legal basis TFEU/art 294 and TFEU/art 194 par 2\\\"."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#countersigned_by>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"A person or organization that countersigned the legislation. Depending on the legal context, a countersignature can indicate that the signed authority undertakes to assume responsibility for texts emanating from a person who is inviolable and irresponsible, (for example a King, Grand Duc or President), or that the authority is in charge of the implementation of the text."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#involved_work>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#Activity> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_responsible_organization>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_participant_organization> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_participant_organization>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#Organization> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#participation_role>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#Participation> .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10190>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalResource> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#ParticipationRole>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>	"Role of an Agent in a Participation"@en .
