    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10288>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#created_legal_expression>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates that a legislative activity created the a legal expression. Typically, a legislative process created the final legal expression of the legislation, as published in the OJ; but this can be used on legislative activities to link to \\\"intermediate\\\" expressions.\nThis property is mostly here for compatibility with FRBRoo, but implementations would prefer using created_a_realization_of_legal_resource to link to the Work level.\nThis could indicate that some Expressions of the final LegalResource were created by the legislative process, and some others were translated afterwards."@en .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10249>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
