    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#produced_manifestation>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates that an activity created a Manifestation.\nThis property is mostly here for compatibility with FRBRoo, but implementations would prefer using created_a_realization_of to link to the Work level.\nThis could indicate that some Manifestation/Formats of the final LegalResource were created by the legislative process, and some others were generated afterwards."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#version_date>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>	"version date"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#cited_by_case_law>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#LegislativeProcess>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"A process of drafting a legislation, covering all stages of the legislation creation, from the initiation to its signature or promulgation to make it a legislation, including readings and assemblies and official signature of the law.\n\nNote that the activity of publishing the legislation in an Official Journal is usually not part of the legislative process, as it usually happens after the draft legislation has become an official legislation."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#DecisionOutcome-Adopted>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates the decision is adopted"@en .
