    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports>	<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#title_alternative>	<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#historyNote>	"v1.3 : broaden the domain to Expression instead of LegalExpression\nv1.2 : changed range from xsd:string to rdfs:Literal"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#ensures_implementation_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates that this LegalResource ensures the implementation of another LegalResource. This implies a legal meaning (contrary to eli:applies).\n\nThis can cover links from national legislation to EU legislation, or links from regional to national legislation. It can also cover links from EU implementing acts to EU legislative acts. In the case of implementation of EU legislation at national level, this covers links to EU regulations, decisions, etc. However the transpositions of EU Directives must be captured with eli:transposes.\n\nLinks between national primary and secondary legislation must be captured by eli:based_on / eli:basis_for."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#activity_label>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#foresees_repeal_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates a LegalResource already published that the future law, if adopted, will repeal. Readers should refer to the definition of the eli:repeals property.\nNote the legal impacts can change in successive versions of the same document."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#activity_start_date>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>	<http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10279> .
