    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10072>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
    <https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/application/pdf>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"created in v1.2"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#ensures_implementation_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#implementation_ensured_by> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#created_a_realization_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates that an Activity created some Work . The works are seen as the \\\"output\\\" of the activity.\n\nThis property is meant to point to the text of the bill, the amendments, the opinions, etc. to point to the final LegalResource published as the outcome of a legislative process, use the alternative property \\\"created_a_realization_of_legal_resource\\\".\n\nFor recording of debates, which are not really \\\"outputs\\\" of the activity, use the alternative property \\\"recorded_in_realization_of\\\".\n\nNote : the naming \\\"created a realization of\\\" is taken from FRBRoo. Since a work is an idea, existing only in people's mind, an activity cannot be simply said to have \\\"created\\\" a work, but really \\\"created an expression of this work\\\"."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#cited_by_case_law>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#LegislativeProcessWorkVersion>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#foresees_based_on>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
    <https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/application/akn+xml>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"created in v1.2"@en .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10209>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalExpression> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#applies>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) somehow conforms with another legislation. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the property transposes. This can be used for example : \n  - when a pre-existing law already conforms to a recent european directive (in that case it does not \"transposes\" it strictly speaking);\n  - when non-EU member states make sure their legislation is conformant with EU law without strictly speaking transposing it;\n  - when a legislation from a local authority conforms with a national legislation;\n\nNote that this should point to a LegalResource, not to a language-specific expression."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#Vote>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#Decision> .
