    <https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/application/pdf;type=scanned>	<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote>	"ELI introduces this value to describe PDF files that are scanned copies of a paper version."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#AmendmentToDraftLegislationWork>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"An amendment created to amend a specific version of a legislation draft.\n\nAmendments can be described and published even if they are not yet voted, or even if they were rejected.\n\nThis is meant to identify both a single amendment, or a document containing a list of amendments.\n\nTo describe a document containing a list of amendments, the relation has_part can be used between the instance of AmendmentToDraftLegislationWork identifying the amendment list and each instance of AmendmentToDraftLegislationWork that identifies an individual amendment within the list."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#is_annex_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates this work or expression is an annex of another one."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#had_voter_intended_abstention>	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/identifier>	"had_voter_intended_abstention" .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10284>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first>	<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalValue-authoritative>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo>	"modified in v1.1"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#foresees_amendment_of>	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/identifier>	"foresees_amendment_of" .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10126>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#Work> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#responsibility_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"An individual, organisation or organisational unit that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.\nThis property should be used when the value cannot be identified by a suitable URI; if a URI is available, the property \"responsibility_of_agent\" should be used."@en .
    <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
