    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#occured_at_stage>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"The stage at which an activity occured.\n\nThe description of the stages themselves is left open for implementers.\n\nExample : The activity \\\"Presentation of Bill 78 of 2018\\\" corresponds to stage \\\"Presentation to the House\\\". The activity \\\"1\u00E8re lecture - Examen en commission du projet de loi 323\\\" corresponds to stage \\\"Examen en commission\\\"."@en .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10109>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>	<http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#consists_of>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf>	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P9_consists_of> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#publisher>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"An entity responsible for making the resource available (definition from Dublin Core).\nThis property should be used when the value cannot be identified by a suitable URI; if a URI is available, the property \"publisher_agent\" should be used."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#LegislativeProcessWorkVersion>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>	"Version of a legislative process work"@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#rightsholder_agent>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain>	<http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#Format> .
    <http://www.example.org/id/.well-known/genid/vb10073>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#rest>	<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil> .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#foreseen_type_document>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates the expected type of the legislation that will be the result of this legislative process.\nThe expected type of legislation can change over time.\n\nThe value must be taken in the ResourceType table, already used for the eli:type_document property."@en .
    <http://data.europa.eu/eli/eli-draft-legislation-ontology#activity_order>	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>	"Indicates the order of this activity in a sequence of activities. Note that the range of this property is xsd:decimal, so it is always possible to order a new activity in between two subsequent existing activities."@en .
